    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To fix a dripping compression faucet, you typically need a replacement washer, a new O-ring, and a small adjustable wrench. First, turn off the water supply to the faucet (or use a bucket to catch the remaining water), then unscrew the faucet handle to expose the valve stem. Once the stem is exposed, use the wrench to tighten the valve seat and replace the old washer and O-ring with new ones. After tightening everything back together, turn the water back on and check for leaks. If the drip persists, you may need to adjust the valve seat or replace the stem itself.",
